<subSubSection id="C30C6572FFC0FFD5FF7AFD09FC8EFAC2" pageId="2" pageNumber="375" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA936F9FFC0FFD5FF7AFD09FB0DFC22" blockId="2.[166,1225,694,1297]" pageId="2" pageNumber="375">
D e s c r i p t i o n. Body broadly-oval (
<figureCitation id="132D2A7CFFC0FFD5FD28FD08FD28FD03" box="[649,739,694,721]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[172,205,1780,1802]" captionTargetBox="[205,1184,413,1749]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1–4. Globicornis (Hadrotoma) ingelehmannae sp. n. (holotype): 1 — habitus, dorsal aspect; 2 — habitus, ventral aspect (→ = prosternal “collar”); 3 — antennal club (schematically); 4 — holotype of G. (H.) ambericus Háva, Prokop et Herrmann, 2006." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452554/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="375">fig. 1–2</figureCitation>
), measurements (in mm): TL 2.7, EW 1.6. Head, pronotum and elytra black; head coarsely punctate, with long black erected setation; palpi entirely black; frontal median ocellus present; antenna with 10 antennomeres, antennal club with 3 antennomeres entirely black (
<figureCitation id="132D2A7CFFC0FFD5FD2CFCA8FD01FCE3" box="[653,714,790,817]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[172,205,1780,1802]" captionTargetBox="[205,1184,413,1749]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1–4. Globicornis (Hadrotoma) ingelehmannae sp. n. (holotype): 1 — habitus, dorsal aspect; 2 — habitus, ventral aspect (→ = prosternal “collar”); 3 — antennal club (schematically); 4 — holotype of G. (H.) ambericus Háva, Prokop et Herrmann, 2006." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452554/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="375">fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Antennal fossa not visible. Eye very large, with black microsetae. Pronotum coarsely punctate as head, with long black erect setation and prominently raised side edge delineated by fine demarcation line. Scutellum triangular, black, without setation. Elytron finely coarsely punctate on humerus, finely on posterior parts, cuticle unicolorous, black without fasciae or spots. Apex of each elytron with long blackish setation. Legs black with black setation; protibia without spines. Metasternum coarsely punctate, with short black setation. Abdominal ventrites with long black setation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA936F9FFC0FFD5FF7AFC49FCA7FBA2" blockId="2.[166,1225,694,1297]" pageId="2" pageNumber="375">
D i a g n o s i s. The new species belong to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D7AFFC0FFD5FC89FC48FB9EFBC2" authority="Latreille, 1829" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1829" box="[808,1109,1014,1040]" class="Insecta" family="Dermestidae" genus="Globicornis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B962EAEBFFC0FFD5FC89FC48FC66FBC2" box="[808,941,1014,1040]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="375">Globicornis</emphasis>
Latreille, 1829
</taxonomicName>
subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D7AFFC0FFD5FF07FBA8FE38FBE2" authority="Erichson, 1846" authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1846" box="[166,499,1046,1072]" class="Insecta" family="Dermestidae" genus="Globicornis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Hadrotoma">
<emphasis id="B962EAEBFFC0FFD5FF07FBA8FEE5FBE2" box="[166,302,1046,1072]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="375">Hadrotoma</emphasis>
Erichson, 1846
</taxonomicName>
according to antennae composed with 10 antennomeres, terminal antennomere triangular and flat, new species differs from the other two known amber species by the characters mentioned in the key below.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA936F9FFC0FFD5FF7AFBC8FBE4FB03" blockId="2.[166,1225,694,1297]" pageId="2" pageNumber="375">
The new species differs from the visually similar species 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D7AFFC0FFD5FCC8FBC9FE3AFB62" authority="Hava, Prokop et Herrmann, 2006" authorityName="Hava, Prokop et Herrmann" authorityYear="2006" class="Insecta" family="Dermestidae" genus="Attagenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoffeinsorum">
<emphasis id="B962EAEBFFC0FFD5FCC8FBC9FBB5FB42" box="[873,1150,1142,1169]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="375">Attagenus hoffeinsorum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF874B08FFC0FFD5FB25FBC8FE3AFB62" author="Hava, J. &amp; Prokop, J. &amp; Herrmann, A." pageId="2" pageNumber="375" pagination="281 - 287" refId="ref1490" refString="Hava, J., Prokop, J., Herrmann, A. 2006. New fossil dermestid beetles (Coleoptera: Dermestidae) from Baltic Amber. Acta Societatis Zoologicae Bohemicae, 69, 281 - 287." type="journal article" year="2006">Háva, Prokop et Herrmann, 2006</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D7AFFC0FFD5FD95FB29FC12FB62" authority="Hava et Bukejs, 2012" authorityName="Hava et Bukejs" authorityYear="2012" box="[564,985,1174,1201]" class="Insecta" family="Dermestidae" genus="Attagenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yantarnyi">
<emphasis id="B962EAEBFFC0FFD5FD95FB29FD07FB62" box="[564,716,1175,1201]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="375">A. yantarnyi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF874B08FFC0FFD5FD76FB28FC12FB62" author="Hava, J. &amp; Bukejs, A." box="[727,985,1174,1201]" pageId="2" pageNumber="375" pagination="155 - 158" refId="ref1530" refString="Hava, J., Bukejs, A. 2012. Attagenus yantarnyi sp. nov., a new species from Baltic Amber (Coleoptera: Dermestidae). Baltic Journal of Coleopterology, 12 (2), 155 - 158." type="journal article" year="2012">Háva et Bukejs, 2012</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by the prosternum forming a “collar” under which mouthparts fit when head is retracted (
<figureCitation id="132D2A7CFFC0FFD5FC45FB08FBEBFB03" box="[996,1056,1206,1233]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,623,645]" captionTargetBox="[174,1226,178,591]" captionTargetId="figure-448@2.[170,1229,174,595]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 5. Head and prothorax lateral aspect, prosternum indicated by arrow." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452556" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452556/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="375">fig. 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA936F9FFC0FFD5FF7AFB69FC8EFAC2" blockId="2.[166,1225,694,1297]" pageId="2" pageNumber="375">E t y m o l o g y. Patronymic, dedicated to commemorate Dr. Inge Lehmann (1888– 1993), an excellent Danish seismologist and geophysicist.</paragraph>
